b'{"data_headers":{"result_code":1},"data":{"information":{"article_id":172,"category_name":"Updates","pr_category_id":"2","title_name":"Update Notification [Addendum]","message":"<div>The update to version 1.3.1 was made available at <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1545890400\\"><\/span>. An automatic update is scheduled to occur at approximately <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1545976800\\"><\/span>.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>To show our gratitude to everyone who performed this update, we will be sending out a Tenfold Summon Voucher. This announcement will be modified after these vouchers have been distributed.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>In version 1.3.1, we changed a feature and fixed certain issues. Details for the update are as follows.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0 Feature changed:<\/div><div>\\u30fb Made it so that the Energized effect is applied to continuous recovery skills and damage due to afflictions or debuffs.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0 Issues fixed:<\/div><div>\\u30fb If you select a Helper from a player who is not your friend and send a friend request after clearing the quest, then select Repeat and send a friend request once more, it becomes impossible to progress.<\/div><div>\\u30fb After clearing a quest, if you send a friend request to a player who has reached their friend limit, it becomes impossible to progress.<\/div><div>\\u30fb The Gauge Accelerator ability is more effective on enemies in the overdrive state than it ought to be.<\/div><div>\\u30fb Fixed other minor issues.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><span style=\\"color: rgb(41, 105, 176);\\"><strong>[Addendum <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1545991200\\"><\/span>]<\/strong><\/span><br>We would like to clarify about the fixed issue noted above: &quot;The Gauge Accelerator ability is more effective on enemies in the overdrive state than it ought to be.&quot;<br>The details of what was fixed are below.<br><br>\\u30fbDetails of the issue<br>The effect of Halloween Elisanne&#39;s &quot;Gauge Accelerator +X%&quot; skill was applied twice to enemies in overdrive mode.<br><br>\\u30fbDetails of the fix<br>We have made it so Halloween Elisanne&#39;s &quot;Gauge Accelerator +X%&quot; skill&#39;s effect is only applied once on enemies in overdrive mode.<br>Consequently, the skill now works as per its description: &quot;Speeds the rate the mode gauge decreases by X%.&quot;<br><br>As a gesture of appreciation for your understanding on this issue, we have sent <span style=\\"color: rgb(41, 105, 176);\\">3 summon tickets<\/span> to all players who have Halloween Elisanne in their Collection.<br><br>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>\\u25a0 Notes:<\/div><div>\\u30fb It may take time for the update information to be reflected in the store.<\/div><div>\\u30fb Players may not be able to perform the update due to their device&#39;s data cache being full.<\/div><div>\\u30fb If you are unable to perform the update, restart your device and then attempt the download from the store.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div><span style=\\"color: rgb(41, 105, 176);\\"><strong>To be added <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1545978600\\"><\/span><\/strong><\/span><br><br>The following will be sent to players who started the game by <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1545976800\\"><\/span><br><br>\\u30fbTenfold Summon Voucher x1<br><br>This will be sent to your goodies box when you log in, and you can claim it until <span class=\\"local_date\\" data-local_date=\\"1546581540\\"><\/span>. This is seven days after it&#39;s sent to your goodie box.<\/div><div><br><\/div><div>Thank you for playing the Dragalia Lost game.<\/div>","start_time":1545890400,"prev_article_id":"146","next_article_id":"176","image_path":"","update_time":1545991774}}}'